2025-06-02  DoccY <alban.mancheron@lirmm.fr>

	* src/Makefile.am, src/Makefile.in, src/kim.cpp, src/kim.h,
	src/kim_settings.cpp, src/kim_settings.h, src/read_analyzer.cpp,
	src/read_analyzer.h, tests/Makefile.in, tests/test_kim_settings.cpp:
	Replace VariantIdentification class by ReadAnalyzer class.
	The ReadAnalyzer uses two parameters:
	- A threshold corresponding to the minimum ratio of k-mers in the read that are associated to some given variant to consider the variant being in the currently analyzed read. The default threshold is 0% (but at least one variant associated k-mer must be present).
	- An error of type I (alpha) to reject a variant that really is in the dataset. The default value is 1%.
	
	
