2024-03-21  DoccY <alban.mancheron@lirmm.fr>

	* src/dna_file_reader.cpp, src/dna_file_reader.h,
	src/file_reader.cpp, src/file_reader.h, src/kim.cpp,
	tests/test_dna_file_reader.cpp:
	Code refactoring for improve reading of DNA files.
	In order to allow the FileReader and DNAFileReader class to be re-used in some other projects, remove the need of the programm Settings binding.
	Now FileReader instances have a single 'warn' public attribute in read/write access and a DNAFileReader instances are built for a constant k-mer length parameter specified on construction.
	
	For any text file, the FileReader (and derived classes) can now:
	- save and restore "bookmarks" on files.
	- change the 'warn' setting at any time.
	
	For DNA files, the DNAFileReader can now:
	- get the sequence ID (its number starting from 1 in the file).
	- compute the total length of the sequence without extracting all the k-mers;
	- extract degenerated k-mers;
	- extract k-mers at any position of the current sequence;
	- go to the beginning of the current sequence;
	- go to the end of the current sequence;
	- go to the next sequence;
	- add or remove callback functions to run each time a new sequence is encountered.
	
	The functional test of the DNAFileReader has been greatly improved in order to reflect the changes.
	
	
